bio.experienceSummary:
As a nurturing caregiver with four years of experience, I'm passionate about enriching the lives of children and supporting families. My journey in childcare began with fulfilling babysitting roles, which fueled my desire to make a positive impact on young minds.

I believe that every child deserves a safe and nurturing environment to thrive. With my patient and calm nature, I provide a stable foundation for children to learn, play, and grow. My creative and imaginative approach to childcare keeps children engaged and entertained, while my friendly and approachable demeanor fosters open communication and trust.

I prioritize clear and effective communication with parents, ensuring that they are well-informed about their child's day and any matters that arise. I adapt to the parents' preferred communication method, whether it's verbal updates during pickup or through their preferred messaging platform.

My approach to household rules is guided by the parents' wishes.

description.originalText: Breana did a great job with our two kids. We will definitely use her in the future.

bio.experienceSummary: I have been working with elderly people for the past 6 years and I am passionate with elderly people I believe myself to be enthusiastic, dynamic, and very flexible. I give care to my best ability and time management will help me finish all tasks given in time. I am friendly and easily approachable.

Hello, I'm Nyaja, and I'm dedicated to providing exceptional child care. With experience as a School-Aged Child-Care and Teen Program Coordinator at the YMCA, I understand the importance of nurturing and enriching young lives. Currently pursuing a master's degree in Social Work, I offer a unique blend of knowledge and empathy in child care. 

I have a proven track record as a babysitter, trusted by multiple families for my reliability and dedication. I'm CPR certified, ensuring your child's safety is a priority. With my own transportation and a strong commitment to punctuality, you can count on me to be there when you need me.

If you're seeking an experienced, educated, and passionate child-care provider, I'd love to connect with you. Feel free to reach out to learn more about how I can be a valuable addition to your family. Your children's well-being is my top priority.

I am 31 with an undergraduate degree. I am the oldest of four children and was always taking care of my younger brothers, while my parents had to work. I have worked for several wonderful families over the past 11 years with children ranging in ages between 4 and 17. I enjoy playing with and watching younger children and also engaging with and guiding teens. Homework help, tutoring and studying come natural and I have no issue helping any age as I have tutoring experience. Lastly, I have a responsible, fun loving, upbeat, reliable and cheerful personality.

description.displayText: I have two daughters, my youngest has Autism. Sam is always on time, has excellent communication skills (always able to reach her), her own vehicle, has no issue staying late, and is wonderful with both my daughters. She is an absolute pleasure and am so pleased and grateful I was able to find her! Her personality, charm, energy, and attention to detail are some of the reasons I chose to hire her in the first place. She still works with us and when she's completed college and graduate school we will be sad to see her go.

bio.experienceSummary:
As a childcare provider with over a year of experience, I'm passionate about nurturing and supporting children's growth and well-being. My calm and friendly demeanor puts children at ease, and my effective communication skills ensure open and honest interactions with parents.

I'm comfortable enforcing household rules and have a knack for making learning fun through engaging activities. From outdoor sports to educational games, I strive to create a stimulating environment that fosters their development.
 
 I am always willing to go the extra mile to help families. Whether it's cooking meals, carpooling, light housekeeping, travel assistance, or supervising swimming, I'm here to provide reliable and compassionate care for your little ones.

Taught children's pottery classes ages 9+
Taught 4+ at after school art programs
Experience babysitting my nephew who is currently 19 months old.
I'm great with kids and my creative side ensures the kids have great time. I am also skilled cook - I make all my meals for myself and others when needed. I have great organizational and cleaning abilities. I have cats and dogs at home so I will be able to help with animal responsibilities alongside house and kids!
Great Multitasker!

Hi, my name is Gricelda. I have 10 years of experience. I am bilingual. I am CPR/First aid training certified. I have my CDA certificate. I have the experience to care for more than once child at once. I can help with Light Housekeeping, children laundry, and tidying up them. I consider myself a trustworthy, responsible, caring, and honest person. I want to be able to provide parents with comfort and security of having someone trustworthy watching their children.

description.originalText: Absolutely amazing to work with. She is attentive, loving, punctual and very gentle with my little one. I highly recommend her .

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi! My name is Aracely, I'm currently a 20-year-old student at Monmouth University and I am currently looking for a babysitting job. 

I first started babysitting at 14 years old. I like working with kids because they are so fun and creative! I feel like a kid on the inside and love playing with them because putting a smile on their face is such a great feeling. On my free time, I love building legos, going on hikes with my dog, and going to concerts. I am patient, motivated, caring, punctual, reliable, and can complete any tasks given to me. 

I have 6 years of babysitting experience ranging from 2 months old to 8 years old.

I am CPR/BLS certified, bilingual (Spanish and English), have the ability to commute, flexible schedule if requested, and can do last minute gigs (date nights, emergency, etc.) 

*CASH ONLY*

description.originalText: For the past 6 months Aracely has been my two-year old daughter’s weekly babysitter and we are so happy she came into our lives! My daughter is always excited to see her and runs to her for a big hug when she arrives. Aracely is very professional and stays in touch with me via text to let me know that my daughter is doing well and updates me on their activities throughout the day. She is a fantastic babysitter; is responsible, caring, honest, communicative and on-time throughout her employment with me. Overall, Aracely is so genuine and a true natural with children and I recommend her wholeheartedly.

bio.experienceSummary: Reliable and caring babysitter with experience providing a safe, fun, and nurturing environment for children of all ages. Bilingual in English and Spanish. Also available for errands, including grocery shopping, pickups/drop-offs, and household tasks. Organized, responsible, and committed to making life easier for busy families.

My name is Alexa and I am 24 years old living in Mountainside, New Jersey. I have experience with children all ages, and can provide multiple references if needed. I have a car and a perfect driving record too. I describe myself as responsible, creative, enthusiastic, and amiable. I love to get creative with fun activities while managing to keep fun and positive control.

description.displayText: I would highly recommend Alexa.  She was very attentive to the children's needs and did a great job.
